The '''Treaty of Den Haag''' (also known as the '''Treaty of The Hague''') was signed on May 16, 1895. The accord established the [[border]]s of [[British New Guinea]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Public debts and state succession |last=Feilchenfeld |first=Ernst H. |page=364 |year=1931 |publisher=[[Macmillan Publishers]] |oclc=3088643 }}</ref>

